/target
Cargo.lock
*.img
*.sqfs
*audit*
.history

# Generated fixtures: oracle tests build SquashFS images into a tempdir,
# but guard against any stray image artifacts landing in the tree.
tests/fixtures/*.img
tests/fixtures/*.sqfs

# Committed offline fixtures: a tiny canonical gzip image (+ its meta) so
# `cargo test` can read a real SquashFS image even on a host without
# squashfs-tools installed. These are intentionally tracked; the blanket
# *.sqfs rule above would otherwise ignore them. The per-compressor +
# feature variants (squashfs-{xz,lz4,zstd,lzo,features}.sqfs) stay ignored
# — regenerate them with scripts/build-squashfs-feature-images.sh.
!test-disks/squashfs-basic.sqfs
!test-disks/*.meta.txt
